 Humansdorp – A 24-year-old man, who was arrested for attempted murder and possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition by the South African Police Service in Humansdorp, appeared in court on Monday. Police in Humansdorp seized the unlicensed 9mm pistol with eleven rounds of ammunition in Humansdorp when he was arrested on Sunday. Sergeant Majola Nkohli said at about 8pm, police received a complaint of an alleged shooting incident at Alwyn Street, Humansdorp. “At the scene, police’s preliminary investigation led them to a spaza shop in Alwyn Street, Humansdorp, where a 9mm pistol with eleven rounds of ammunition was seized. “Police arrested 24-year-old man for possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition,” said Sgt Nkohli. “The suspect was also charged for a case of attempted murder and was due to appear at the Humansdorp Magistrate’s Court on Monday for charges of attempted murder, possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition.” Sergeant Nkohli said that the firearm was apparently stolen in the Free State. “A preliminary investigation has revealed that a CZ P-09 firearm that was allegedly found in possession of the suspect was stolen in Free State in January this year.” Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. 